  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler framework defines nine core plugin extension points through Go interfaces located primarily in staging/src/k8s.io/kube-scheduler/framework/interface.go, which serves as the public API. These extension points are: PreFilter (PreFilterPlugin), Filter (FilterPlugin), PostFilter (PostFilterPlugin), PreScore (PreScorePlugin), Score (ScorePlugin), Reserve (ReservePlugin), PreBind (PreBindPlugin), Bind (BindPlugin), and PostBind (PostBindPlugin). All these interfaces embed the base Plugin interface which requires a Name() method. Supporting interfaces include PreFilterExtensions (for incremental AddPod/RemovePod operations), ScoreExtensions (for NormalizeScore operations), EnqueueExtensions (for efficient pod queue management), and SignPlugin (for batching optimizations). The framework implementation is in pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go, which contains the frameworkImpl struct that maintains plugin slices for each extension point and provides Run* methods to execute them: RunPreFilterPlugins, RunFilterPlugins, RunPreScorePlugins, RunScorePlugins, RunReservePluginsReserve/Unreserve, RunPermitPlugins, RunPreBindPlugins, RunPreBindPreFlights, RunBindPlugins, and RunPostBindPlugins. The extensionPoint struct in framework.go groups plugin configuration and implementation slices, while getExtensionPoints method returns all nine extension points in order. Plugin registration is managed through the Registry type (a map of PluginFactory functions) defined in pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go. Plugin configuration is defined in pkg/scheduler/apis/config/types.go via the Plugins struct which contains PluginSet fields for each extension point, and versioned configuration types are in pkg/scheduler/apis/config/v1/types.go. The pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go file provides local framework types and the pkg/scheduler/metrics/metrics.go file defines metrics constants for each extension point."
}

